WEBVTT

00:04.571 --> 00:05.539 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening.

00:05.572 --> 00:07.441 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:07.474 --> 00:11.912 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On the "NewsHour" tonight: As
the CIA concludes
Russia acted to sway the U.S.
election in

00:11.945 --> 00:16.783 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Donald Trump's favor, we talk
with one of
the bipartisan group of senators
calling for

00:16.817 --> 00:18.652 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
an investigation.

00:18.685 --> 00:23.523 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Then: the future of Obamacare --
Health and
Human Services Secretary
®MDNM /MD-BO /Sylvia

00:23.557 --> 00:27.895 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Burwell on the fate of the
president's signature
law under a Trump
administration.

00:27.928 --> 00:31.365 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SYLVIA MATHEWS BURWELL, U.S.
Health and Human
Services Secretary: It's like a
game of Jenga,

00:31.398 --> 00:35.702 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
where you have the puzzle
pieces, and if you
pull one out, the thing will
topple.

00:35.736 --> 00:44.344 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And the Music
City feels the
pressure -- how Nashville's
booming housing

00:44.378 --> 00:46.947 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
market is threatening its
historic culture.

00:46.980 --> 00:49.616 align:left position:25%,start line:80% size:75%
AUBREY PRESTON,
Developer/Philanthropist:
I believe in Music City.

00:49.650 --> 00:55.322 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It would be the equivalent of,
in Egypt, them
allowing one of their three
pyramids or something

00:55.355 --> 00:56.723 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to be torn down.

00:56.757 --> 00:59.026 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's just an impossibility that
this building
would be torn down.

00:59.059 --> 01:06.867 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All that and more
on tonight's
"PBS NewsHour."

01:06.900 --> 01:09.703 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

01:09.736 --> 01:19.680 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: There's a split
tonight between
Donald Trump and his own
Republican Party,

01:19.713 --> 01:25.285 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
at issue, serious allegations
that the Russians
were playing spy games during
the presidential

01:25.319 --> 01:26.386 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
campaign.

01:26.420 --> 01:28.221 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
John Yang begins our coverage.

01:28.255 --> 01:33.026 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Top congressional
Republicans put
themselves at odds with
president-elect Trump

01:33.060 --> 01:38.165 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
today, calling for
investigations into possible
Russian attempts to influence
the election.

01:38.198 --> 01:40.100 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

01:40.133 --> 01:41.935 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MITCH MCCONNELL (R-KY), Majority
Leader: Obviously,
any foreign breach of
cyber-security measures

01:41.969 --> 01:46.740 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
are disturbing, and I strongly
condemn any
such efforts.

01:46.773 --> 01:50.277 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Well, let me just speak for
myself.

01:50.310 --> 01:51.712 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
The Russians are not our
friends.

01:51.745 --> 01:53.780 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
DONALD TRUMP (R),
President-Elect: I think
it's just another excuse.

01:53.814 --> 01:58.118 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: On Sunday, Mr. Trump
dismissed
the CIA's conclusion that the
Russians were

01:58.151 --> 02:01.188 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
trying to help him win as
ridiculous.

02:01.221 --> 02:04.958 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
He pointed to apparent
disagreements between
the spy agency and the FBI.

02:04.992 --> 02:07.027 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: I have great
respect for them.

02:07.060 --> 02:12.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But if you read the stories, the
various stories,
they're disputing.

02:12.766 --> 02:16.069 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And certain groups don't
necessarily agree.

02:16.103 --> 02:18.839 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Personally, it could be Russia.

02:18.872 --> 02:20.807 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It -- I don't really think it
is.

02:20.841 --> 02:21.808 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
But who knows?

02:21.842 --> 02:22.809 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I don't know either.

02:22.843 --> 02:24.611 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They don't know and I don't
know.

02:24.644 --> 02:27.848 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: This morning, he
tweeted that:
"If the election results were
the opposite

02:27.881 --> 02:34.588 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
and we tried to play the
Russia/CIA card,
it would be called conspiracy
theory."

02:34.621 --> 02:39.860 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Russia is also an issue with a
potential secretary
of state in the Trump
administration, ExxonMobil

02:39.893 --> 02:41.995 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
CEO Rex Tillerson.

02:42.029 --> 02:46.800 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He's done a lot of business
there and has
close ties to President Vladimir
Putin.

02:46.833 --> 02:50.604 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That's a reason for concern, say
some Senate
Republicans, including John
McCain.

02:50.637 --> 02:52.339 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

02:52.372 --> 02:54.841 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN MCCAIN (R), Arizona: Maybe
those ties
are strictly commercial and got
to do with

02:54.875 --> 02:57.477 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
his business in the oil
business.

02:57.511 --> 02:58.478 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Fine.

02:58.512 --> 03:00.947 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But we will give him a fair
hearing.

03:00.981 --> 03:02.849 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
But is it a matter of concern?

03:02.883 --> 03:04.751 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Certainly, it should be a matter
of concern.

03:04.785 --> 03:09.656 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Meanwhile, the
president-elect's
challenge to the longstanding
U.S. one-China

03:09.689 --> 03:13.693 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
policy brought a stern warning
from the Chinese
Foreign Ministry.

03:13.727 --> 03:17.431 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GENG SHUANG, Chinese Foreign
Ministry Spokesperson
(through translator): I want to
stress that

03:17.464 --> 03:21.068 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the Taiwan issue involves
China's sovereignty
and territorial integrity.

03:21.101 --> 03:26.139 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
If such a foundation is
disrupted and undermined,
the sound and steady growth of
our relations

03:26.173 --> 03:28.008 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
would be impossible.

03:28.041 --> 03:32.479 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Today, Mr. Trump
officially named
his choice for secretary of
homeland security,

03:32.512 --> 03:38.218 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
retired Marine Four-Star General
John Kelly,
a veteran of four decades in the
Corps.

03:38.251 --> 03:43.824 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Kelly most recently headed U.S.
Southern Command,
overseeing military operations
in Central

03:43.857 --> 03:45.659 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and South America.

03:45.692 --> 03:50.530 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In that role, he also worked
with Homeland
Security to stop the smuggling
of immigrants.

03:50.564 --> 03:56.136 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He's the third general Mr. Trump
has picked
for a major post, but he is also
a Gold Star

03:56.169 --> 03:57.571 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
parent.

03:57.604 --> 04:01.775 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
His son, a Marine 1st
lieutenant, was killed
in Afghanistan in 2010.

04:01.808 --> 04:06.713 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The president-elect also named
Goldman Sachs
president Gary Cohn to head the
White House

04:06.746 --> 04:09.015 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
National Economic Council.

04:09.049 --> 04:11.418 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm John
Yang.

04:11.451 --> 04:15.088 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And two
developments in election
recounts today.

04:15.122 --> 04:22.162 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A federal judge refused to order
one in Pennsylvania,
as Green Party candidate Jill
Stein wanted.

04:22.195 --> 04:25.899 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And a new tally ended in
Wisconsin, with little
change.

04:25.932 --> 04:28.301 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Donald Trump won both states.

04:28.335 --> 04:33.173 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Among those voicing concern
about Russia's
attempts to influence the
presidential election,

04:33.206 --> 04:38.745 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a bipartisan group of senators
who called
for an investigation into the
cyber-attacks

04:38.778 --> 04:42.482 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that they say should alarm every
American.

04:42.516 --> 04:47.320 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Jack Reed, the ranking member of
the Senate
Armed Services Committee is one
of those senators,

04:47.354 --> 04:50.090 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and he says he has no reason to
doubt the
CIA's conclusions.

04:50.123 --> 04:51.591 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

04:51.625 --> 04:54.194 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JACK REED (D), Rhode Island:
They definitely
intervened in the election.

04:54.227 --> 05:00.500 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They collected information
against both Democrats
and Republicans, and they seemed
to only have

05:00.534 --> 05:05.505 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
released information with
respect to the Democratic
candidate.

05:05.539 --> 05:09.609 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
The motivation, that is
something that we're
going to continue to probe.

05:09.643 --> 05:16.750 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But it seems -- it seems that
they were interested
in disrupting the Democratic
campaign as much

05:16.783 --> 05:18.151 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
as they could.

05:18.185 --> 05:20.187 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: You don't have
any question
about that conclusion?

05:20.220 --> 05:24.591 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Because the FBI, as you know,
it's reported
that they are holding back on
ascribing a

05:24.624 --> 05:25.592 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
motive here.

05:25.625 --> 05:27.460 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

05:27.494 --> 05:31.464 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JACK REED: Well, there is a
difference between
a motive and what happened on
the ground,

05:31.498 --> 05:33.266 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
if you will.

05:33.300 --> 05:38.338 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What seems to be clear is that
they had been
able to enter into the computer
systems of

05:38.371 --> 05:44.377 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
both the Republicans and the
Democrats, and
that they through proxies
disseminated information

05:44.411 --> 05:49.082 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
about the Democratic candidate,
didn't in
any significant way do so with
the Republicans.

05:49.115 --> 05:54.254 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Could you question motivations,
but it seems
clear that they had a goal and
objective to

05:54.287 --> 05:58.658 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
provide information that would
be detrimental
to the Democratic candidate.

05:58.692 --> 06:02.162 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And what other
explanation
could there be other than
wanting to help

06:02.195 --> 06:03.363 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Donald Trump?

06:03.396 --> 06:05.131 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

06:05.165 --> 06:09.569 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JACK REED: It -- the only other
plausible
explanation would be just so to
sow general

06:09.603 --> 06:11.404 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
confusion.

06:11.438 --> 06:16.676 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But at some point, they clearly
seem to suggest
a preference in terms of who
they were going

06:16.710 --> 06:20.747 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to attack or provide detrimental
information
about.

06:20.780 --> 06:22.582 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And that was the Democratic
candidate.

06:22.616 --> 06:26.553 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: What does this
represent to
you, Senator Reed, as somebody
who has looked

06:26.586 --> 06:28.989 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
at intelligence for as long as
you have?

06:29.022 --> 06:30.757 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

06:30.790 --> 06:35.862 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JACK REED: Well, it demonstrates
the practice
that the Russians have of
surreptitiously

06:35.895 --> 06:42.802 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
using cyber and other techniques
to involve
themselves in elections, to
distort elections.

06:42.836 --> 06:44.638 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It happened overseas.

06:44.671 --> 06:48.141 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And now, unfortunately, it has
happened dramatically
in the United States.

06:48.174 --> 06:50.076 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And so we have to be aware of
this.

06:50.110 --> 06:55.615 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That is why Senator McCain and I
are working
to set up a subcommittee to look
at this issue,

06:55.649 --> 07:02.922 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
but longer term to look at the
cyber-capabilities
of Russia in many different
dimensions.

07:02.956 --> 07:08.828 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But the first issue is trying to
get all the
facts that we can out about
their participation

07:08.862 --> 07:14.134 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in this election cycle, because
we have to
be able to show the American
public that in

07:14.167 --> 07:20.307 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
two years or at any time in the
future, our
elections are not determined by
surreptitious

07:20.340 --> 07:23.910 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
activity of foreign intelligence
services;
they're determined by the
voters.

07:23.943 --> 07:28.248 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, I'm sure,
as you know,
the president-elect, Donald
Trump, is saying

07:28.281 --> 07:30.650 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
he doesn't believe that the
Russians did this.

07:30.684 --> 07:33.486 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He says he's not at all sure
they did the
hacking.

07:33.520 --> 07:38.925 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He says it could have been a man
sitting on
a bed somewhere.

07:38.958 --> 07:42.662 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
How do you -- what do you say to
his reaction
to all this?

07:42.696 --> 07:44.197 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

07:44.230 --> 07:48.234 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JACK REED: Well, it seems quite
obvious that
this was done by the Russians.

07:48.268 --> 07:51.004 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Our intelligence services have
indicated it.

07:51.037 --> 07:53.440 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
They have done so very
carefully.

07:53.473 --> 07:57.777 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
To disregard the obvious is not
a good trait
in a leader in any situation.

07:57.811 --> 08:00.413 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: To disregard the
obvious?

08:00.447 --> 08:01.481 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

08:01.514 --> 08:02.615 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
JACK REED: Yes.

08:02.649 --> 08:05.352 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, do you want
to elaborate
on that?

08:05.385 --> 08:07.187 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

08:07.220 --> 08:10.457 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JACK REED: Well, it seems that
the facts are
overwhelming that there is the
involvement

08:10.490 --> 08:18.131 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of the Russians in the election,
the involvement
not only in terms of penetrating
Democratic

08:18.164 --> 08:21.968 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
operatives and organizations,
but also, as
the intelligence community
concluded also,

08:22.001 --> 08:23.303 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
the Republican National
Committee.

08:23.336 --> 08:24.571 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
So, they were involved.

08:24.604 --> 08:28.508 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And that seems to be not an
issue of contention.

08:28.541 --> 08:34.848 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And to simply deny that is to
deny what to
me appears increasingly to be
obvious, a fact.

08:34.881 --> 08:40.286 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Senator, what
would be different
between the investigation that
you and some

08:40.320 --> 08:45.392 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Republican senators are calling
for and the
investigation that President
Obama has called

08:45.425 --> 08:47.994 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
for inside the administration to
be done by
the inauguration?

08:48.027 --> 08:49.863 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

08:49.896 --> 08:55.568 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JACK REED: Well, the president
is able to
use the intelligence agencies
and other agencies

08:55.602 --> 09:02.175 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to vet the information, to
protect sources
and methods, to come up with all
that could

09:02.208 --> 09:03.710 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
released to the public.

09:03.743 --> 09:06.513 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Our investigation, I hope, will
build off
of that.

09:06.546 --> 09:12.652 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
I hope the document the
president us is available,
so we have a common base of
facts and knowledge.

09:12.685 --> 09:19.926 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And from there, we can ask other
questions
that I think are relevant going
forward: What

09:19.959 --> 09:21.694 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
can we do to prevent this in the
future?

09:21.728 --> 09:29.102 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think also it raises again the
issue that
has been so contentious over the
last several

09:29.135 --> 09:35.208 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
months about the president-elect
being much
more open and candid in his
financial dealings,

09:35.241 --> 09:40.480 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
so that there is absolutely no
question of
any type of bias towards any
institution or

09:40.513 --> 09:41.848 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
individual or country.

09:41.881 --> 09:44.117 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, two other
questions.

09:44.150 --> 09:49.722 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
One is, what should the U.S. do
if this is
proven that the Russians did
this hacking

09:49.756 --> 09:54.527 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and if they did it for the
reason that it
appears that they did?

09:54.561 --> 09:56.296 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
