16:59.051 --> 17:01.520 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MICHAEL MCFAUL, Former U.S.
Ambassador to
Russia: Well, for some of us,
it's not news.

17:01.554 --> 17:05.892 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Some of us have been talking and
writing about
this for many months now,
especially after

17:05.925 --> 17:10.630 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the hacking of the DNC computers
and the data
dump from WikiLeaks.

17:10.663 --> 17:15.401 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think the two pieces of news
that are new
is that the intelligence
community is now

17:15.434 --> 17:20.373 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
claiming that they have evidence
to show that
the Russians gave it to
WikiLeaks.

17:20.406 --> 17:21.374 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
That was uncertain.

17:21.407 --> 17:23.109 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Now we know that.

17:23.142 --> 17:26.879 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the second piece is about
the Republican
-- the hacking into the
Republican side.

17:26.913 --> 17:29.515 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They now have evidence to show
that.

17:29.548 --> 17:35.521 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And what it all means to me, to
be clear,
my bottom line is, we need an
independent,

17:35.554 --> 17:38.958 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
bipartisan commission to
investigate this.

17:38.991 --> 17:41.794 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
