administration
to do their review.

17:41.827 --> 17:45.431 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, frankly, it's not enough to
have hearings
on it at the U.S. Congress.

17:45.464 --> 17:48.901 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This is way too big to be
handled in those
places.

17:48.935 --> 17:50.569 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We need to know the facts.

17:50.603 --> 17:54.006 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And, here, I agree with
president-elect Trump
in the piece you played with
him.

17:54.040 --> 17:56.575 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He said several times, we don't
know.

17:56.609 --> 17:59.145 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Well, as an academic, I want to
know the facts.

17:59.178 --> 18:02.982 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think the only way you're
going to get
it is if you set up that
commission.

18:03.015 --> 18:05.518 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: James Woolsey,
do you agree;
is that the right course?

18:05.551 --> 18:09.155 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JAMES WOOLSEY, Former CIA
Director: I don't
see anything wrong with a
well-assembled commission

18:09.188 --> 18:11.290 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
going into an important issue.

18:11.324 --> 18:15.294 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think what needs to be focused
on here,
though, from the beginning is
that we have

18:15.328 --> 18:18.197 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
got a couple of different things
going on.

18:18.230 --> 18:21.634 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And conflating them causes a lot
of confusion.

18:21.667 --> 18:27.039 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
One is what the Soviets and then
now the Russians
call disinformation,
dezinformatsiya, otherwise

18:27.073 --> 18:29.175 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
known as lying.

18:29.208 --> 18:34.780 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And they propagate
disinformation throughout
the world on all sorts of
subjects.

18:34.814 --> 18:40.686 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But they particularly focus on
organizations
and groups that embody values
that they find

18:40.720 --> 18:45.925 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
abhorrent, such as the Catholic
Church and
Judaism.

18:45.958 --> 18:54.133 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They are apparently moving into
disseminating
disinformation about Western
political parties.

18:54.166 --> 18:59.505 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's not any different in
principle from what
they have been doing for
decades.

18:59.538 --> 19:03.843 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think that's one set of things
that's going
on.

19:03.876 --> 19:11.350 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Another set of things that
conceivably could
go on is hacking into the
records of the voting

19:11.384 --> 19:13.886 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
in order to change those votes.

19:13.919 --> 19:21.694 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I don't know that there is any
indication
that we have that this latter is
taking place,

19:21.727 --> 19:26.232 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
counting people who are dead as
voters and
the sort of things that you read
about in

19:26.265 --> 19:28.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the American system.

19:28.134 --> 19:40.846 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, I think, insofar as someone
says that
the Russians were not
participating in anything

19:40.880 --> 19:46.886 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
may not be correct, because they
may have
been participating in
disseminating disinformation,

19:46.919 --> 19:55.027 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
but not participating in what
most of us think
of as voting fraud, namely,
counting people

19:55.061 --> 19:56.629 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
who vote who are dead and so
forth.

19:56.662 --> 19:59.098 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: James Woolsey,
I hear some
hesitation on your part.

19:59.131 --> 20:03.702 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Do you doubt the credibility of
your former
agency in coming to this
conclusion?

20:03.736 --> 20:10.176 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JAMES WOOLSEY: No, I think
they're conflating
-- they may well be conflating
the issues

20:10.209 --> 20:11.677 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
as well.

20:11.710 --> 20:15.548 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
One really needs to separate
these out and
talk about them separately.

20:15.581 --> 20:18.918 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I don't know what the CIA would
decide.

20:18.951 --> 20:23.289 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I haven't read anything they
have written
